19/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Turkish Armed Forces donated military equipment to the Bosnian Federation Army on Monday (18 August).
According to an official statement by the Joint Command of the Federation Army, the donation includes vehicles with built-in telecommunications equipment, transporters and tanks.
Turkey has also offered to finance the modification of old equipment and the training of 27 soldiers and officers.
The Federation Army calls Ankara a "proven friend".
(Onasa, Anadolu Agency - 18/08/03)
